been sensing weird vibes.

14:33.204 --> 14:37.075
♪ SUSPENSEFUL SYNTH ♪

14:45.583 --> 14:48.387
No I'm telling you,
there's something off.

14:49.387 --> 14:52.523
Look, I've said
it once, I'll say it again.

14:53.091 --> 14:55.193
It had to be somebody who...

14:55.226 --> 14:58.230
- Would you let me just do my job?
- Okay? We're exploring all the

14:58.263 --> 15:01.633
options and when someone has
an alibi, quite frankly it makes

15:01.666 --> 15:03.268
things harder.

15:03.301 --> 15:06.538
No. No there's something off.

15:08.673 --> 15:12.611
What about that girl that uh,
Grace Fisher mentioned on her

15:12.644 --> 15:14.179
voicemail?

15:14.212 --> 15:18.417
Taylor, this is
Detective Hoffman.

15:21.753 --> 15:24.523
Okay, thank you for your help
Mr. Scott. I can take it from

15:24.556 --> 15:26.058
here.

15:26.091 --> 15:29.995
Oh, well please
take good care of her.

15:30.028 --> 15:35.000
She is my top
pupil in class and on stage.

15:35.033 --> 15:36.143
Okay, you have
nothin' to worry about.

15:36.167 --> 15:38.070
I'm just
gonna ask her a few questions.

15:39.204 --> 15:41.040
Sure.

15:46.111 --> 15:49.114
Okay, I'm the uh, lead
detective on the Grace Fisher

15:49.147 --> 15:53.719
murder case.
Did you know the victim?

15:53.752 --> 15:57.289
No. Uh, not really.

15:57.322 --> 15:59.424
Did you ever have
any interaction with her?

15:59.457 --> 16:02.527
Freshman year. I, I met
with her a couple times.

16:02.560 --> 16:05.296
Okay. And those conversations,
what were they pertaining to?

16:06.698 --> 16:08.300
Taylor?

16:08.333 --> 16:10.267
Sorry what,
what was the question?

16:10.301 --> 16:12.380
What were you and Miss
Fisher discussing freshman year?

16:12.404 --> 16:15.741
She was counseling me
for my dad's disappearance.

16:17.509 --> 16:20.045
It didn't, it didn't help much,

16:20.078 --> 16:23.749
but time kinda
healed that wound.

16:27.352 --> 16:31.423
Before Miss Fisher was murdered
she left a voicemail for Arthur.

16:33.191 --> 16:37.029
She mentioned you. Now we have
reason to believe that your life

16:37.062 --> 16:41.433
may be in danger. Have you
noticed anything unusual around

16:41.466 --> 16:43.168
here lately?

16:46.538 --> 16:51.476
Unusual? Life threatening? No,

16:51.509 --> 16:55.214
not at all. Am I gonna be okay?

16:56.114 --> 17:00.619
You need to stay
careful. Okay? Be vigilant.

17:01.686 --> 17:03.489
This is my office number.

17:05.256 --> 17:07.159
If anything else happens or you

17:07.192 --> 17:08.402
hear anything more pertaining to

17:08.425 --> 17:13.064
Grace, please call. Get in touch
with me day or night, okay?

17:13.098 --> 17:15.032
Okay.

17:15.733 --> 17:16.800
Let's go.

17:22.240 --> 17:26.377
♪ EERIE SYNTH ♪

17:37.856 --> 17:39.725
That's it?

17:40.391 --> 17:44.129
What? You know how my stomach
gets before a performance.

17:44.162 --> 17:47.066
I eat whatever
I want whenever I want so.

17:48.500 --> 17:51.236
I have a lot on my mind.

17:51.269 --> 17:56.208
Shh, shh, shh. Oh Romeo,
wherefore art thou Romeo?

17:57.642 --> 17:59.644
I want to perform for him.

17:59.677 --> 18:01.847
That show would
be over before it even started.

18:02.447 --> 18:04.082
What show?

18:04.549 --> 18:06.618
Don't worry about
it. Just talking about

18:06.651 --> 18:07.752
the last performance.

18:07.786 --> 18:11.290
Me worried? No, no, no,
no, no. See I wasn't worried.

18:11.789 --> 18:16.360
